sql:
SELECT bid_no
FROM bids
WHERE bid_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM bids
WHERE department_id = (SELECT department_id FROM departments WHERE department_name = 'Procurement');

SELECT bid_no, start_date
FROM bids
ORDER BY bid_no;

external_knowledge:
A vendor is considered active if they have participated in at least one bid, as indicated by a bid count greater than 0; 
The number of bids a vendor has placed refers to the count of bid-vendor associations; 
The average price a vendor has quoted is the mean of the prices they have quoted across all their bids.
